# Alert Properties

Time : Shows when the alert was created
Name : Summary of what happened
Severity : Defines the urgency of the alert as low, medium or high
Status : Informs someone working on the alert, if the alert was triaged or not
Verdict : Determine if it's a true positive ( Real threat) or false positive (No threat)
Assignee : The anlyst that was assigned to the alert
Description : Here the assignee tells us what was the alert about and how he triaged the alert


# Allert Prioritisation

Using any SIEM tool or EDR

1. Filter your alerts :
Don't take alerts that are already reviewed, take only new, yet unseen and unresolved alerts.

2. Sort by severity :
Start with critical, high, medium and finally low alerts, because major threats cause more damage than medium low threats.

3.Sort by time : 
Start with the oldest alert and end with the newest alerts.
